thread.title: Public Bank reports higher FY16 earnings

author: JOSEPH CHIN
title: Public Bank reports higher FY16 earnings
text: 41 PM Public Bank reports higher FY16 earnings KUALA LUMPUR: Public Bank Bhd reported higher earnings of RM5.20bil in the financial year ended Dec 31, 2016 (FY16). It announced a dividend of 32 sen a share similar to a year ago The banking group said on Thursday the earnings were up 2.8% from the RM5.06bil in FY15. Its revenue rose to RM20.10bil from RM19.18bil in FY15. For the fourth quarter ended Dec 31, 2016, its earnings dipped slightly to RM1.48bil from RM1.49bil a year ago. However, its revenue increased to RM5.08bil from RM4.93bil. Earnings per share were 38.4 sen compared with 38.65 sen.
